race.comment: SPOOKY HOOK (1) is in hot form after clocking a speedy 27.39 victory two back then followed up with a 27.41 win at Mandurah over 488m last time. Flying lately and expected to go close again. TRANSCENDENT (3) is worth forgiving last start after finishing fifth (30.80) from Box 3 at this track over 520m. Has a solid record from this box including two wins and a minor placing. Better than last start and can bounce back. TORINO (2) was an effortless winner two back scoring by 1.5 lengths but could manage only midfield last time when finished 4th and beaten 6 lengths at this track (30.17). Key runner on best form. SPENCER (8) has strong claims after a top-three finish in good time last time out.
